cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  Hi Everyone and welcome to today's Precision Club session, in which the plan is that we'll be looking at the latest addition to our Asking Bid arsenal, Sigma.

This should be a fairly easy week for those who followed the session on Alpha, but will be a little incomprehensible to those not familiar with Alpha For anyone who has not been to the previous sessions on Asking Bids  this is certainly not a "basic" topic.

If you're not completely familiar with "basic Precision Openings and responses, then this will be a difficult session for you to follow or get much from.

If you have not already done so, please have a look at the notes I have prepared on Precision Club bidding.

You can find these on: ^*h http://ocp.pigpen.org.uk/index.php ^*n.

You will DEFINITELY benefit from these onscreen in the background for reference during this session <grin>.

http://ocp.pigpen.org.uk/Sigma.php If you are new to Asking Bids then there's no way you're going to absorb everything we cover tonight, so please do visit the site and read through the Asking Bid section at your leisure.

If you want download one of the Precision system documents on the site 

    See  ^*h http://ocp.pigpen.org.uk/Documents.php ^*n ).

They are fairly large (around 500k) but cover this stuff in more detail.|
