fp|t-title|at|Recap  of  Alpha|fp||at|^^^^|
cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  Okay, Since Sigma relates SOLELY to Alpha, I'm going to recap Alpha briefly.

Alpha is a primary Asking Bid and is always the FIRST Asking Bid in a sequence if it is used at all.

Alpha is found in only 3 places (except in the Complex System): 

^c@.  New Suit Bid (Not the low-level Relay Beta) over a positive response to 1@C

^c@.  2NT rebid over a  1NT,  2@C  or  2@D  response to  1@C  is Alpha in the Relay Suit

^c@.  @2Jump-Shift over a  1@D, 1NT  or  2@C Opening
^b@2
Alpha Asks about support for Opener's suit (the suit bid) and about Responder's general level of Controls.

There are 4 basic responses and then the scale becomes open-ended scale covering the cases where 

Responder has GOOD Support (Hxxx or better) and 4+ Controls.



(see next page)|
