So for the purposes of this session, we are only interested in occasions when Alpha gets a 3-step or greater response and so the suit is agreed as trumps

In the event of a NEGATIVE response to Alpha, an immediate repeat in the same suit is Theta (a Response 
showing  Hx or xxx  agrees the suit now) and an immediate bid in a new suit is Iota (or Gamma if Responder's suit).

We covered those last week.

In the event of a 3 step response to Alpha, a bid in the next suit up is Relay Beta and Sigma is the bid above that.

Over a 4 (or more) step response the next bid up is Sigma the Relay Beta is the bid above that.

So the Repeat of the Trump suit is  ^*bSigma^*n  and a    ^*bbid in the suit ABOVE^*n    the agreed suit is  ^*bBeta^*n.

O, any questions about Alpha before we have a look at Sigma ?|
