cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|  Sigma is used to check on trump solidity by asking Responder to clarify their trump holding.
|lg|c|at|
The thing to remember is that trump "support" for the purposes of Alpha is an "all or nothing" affair.

If you have  ^*b Hxx ^*n or ^*b xxxx ^*n (or better)  in the suit then you show support.
It's only if you have  ^*b 4+ controls ^*n  AND at least ^*b Hxxx ^*n in the suit that the "asker" has any indication as to how good that support is.

Sigma fills that gap in that it allows the Alpha Asker to ascertain exactly how good Responder's trump support is after a POSITIVE response.


This the only way the strong hand can check on trump solidity (except perhaps by a process of elimination).

As was said earlier

Over a  3 or 4 step  positive response to Alpha ^m(0-3 ctrls, ^*b Hxx ^*n or ^*b xxxx ^*n or better)
^c an immediate repeat of the agreed trump suit BELOW game level is ^*b Sigma^*n.

Over a  5+ step positive response to Alpha      ^m(level minus 1  ctrls,  ^*bHxxx ^*n or better)
^c a bid in the next bid up is ^*b Sigma^*n
^c (no relay Beta is required)


the Steps for  Sigma  follow...|
