at|^*bisabable:^*n     ? Does it cause a conflict when 3NT could be   Relay Beta   and also  Repeat Sigma ?

|cp|red|at|^*bOliverC:^*n|cp||at|   No, because Repeat Sigma ALWAYS take precedence over Relay Beta.  

Similarly, an initial Sigma (after a 3 or 4 step response to Alpha) is in the trump suit itself, and Relay beta is NEVER in the trump suit.

Over a 5 step or greater response to Alpha, we know Responder's exact number of controls anyway, so  Relay Beta  doesn't arise.

For example Opener has     @SK10983  @HA  @DKQJ107 @CAK      The Bidding goes 

^c 1@C  -  1@H  -  1@S(Alpha)  -  2@H(Supp, 4+)

With 4+ Controls, Partner MUST have the 2 sharp Aces, and so it looks 6@S is a shoe-in.

But Opener really needs to know how good Partner's Spade support is and no amount of Epsilons elsewhere will tell him whether partner has the  @sQ  or  @SJ   of Spades.

So Sigma is most often used when Opener is pretty strong, but has a relatively weak trump suit, so trump solidity is the most critical factor.|
